A sequential combustor assembly for a gas turbine assembly comprises: 
• a first-stage combustor (8) comprising at least one first burner (20) fed with at least one first fuel and configured to generate, in use, at least one first flame (22); 
• a second-stage combustor (9) arranged downstream the first-stage combustor (8) and fed by the hot gas leaving the first-stage combustor (8); the second-stage combustor (9) comprising at least one second burner (21) fed with at least one second fuel and being configured to generate, in use, a second flame (23); 
• an air supply circuit (25) comprising: 
- a first line (30) configured to supply air to the at least one first burner (20) of the first-stage combustor (8); 
- a second line (31) configured to supply air downstream the at least one first flame (22) and upstream the second-stage combustor (9); 
- an adjusting device (33) configured to adjust a first air flow rate in the first line (30) and a second air flow rate in the second line (31) so as to control the ratio between the first air flow rate and the second air flow rate.
